data.content:
Yes — the direct cast will throw an `InvalidCastException` instead of a clean test failure if the type is wrong. Use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>`, which both verifies the type and returns the cast object:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This gives you a clear assertion failure message on type mismatch instead of an exception, and the generic overload (MSTest v3+) returns the cast value so you can keep testing properties.
